page.title: 04Oakenshaw Wood.
page.content: {Oakenshaw Wood},Coldfield Drive, Redditch .You may visit the trail at any time.A trail guide is available from Redditch Borough Council. The nature trail has nine stopping places and starts at the pond.Once known as Tanner's Wood it is an ancient wood.The wood is mainly deciduous but there are some interesting{Evergreens {like Douglas Fir.}Shrubs like{hazel {and hawthorn grow there}.There are interesting birds to be seen such as The Greater{Spotted Woodpecker}and the {Tree-Creeper.}Other wild-life includes the{Grey Squirrel}and{rabbits.}The {pond}has fish and amphibians.If you get a permit from{The Arrow Valley {Social Club}you may fish there. Near by are two other nice places to visit,{Southcrest Woods}and{Lodge {Pool.
